// Adversarial: Supernova evolution chip is injected via chip_selections before play begins.
// Supernova is a multi-stage evolution (Piercing Shot x3 + Surge) that spawns additional bolts
// and fires shockwaves on cell destruction. Prism breaker already starts with multiple bolts,
// so Supernova's spawning pressure combines with Prism's native multi-bolt behaviour to stress
// bolt count and entity lifecycle under Dense layout. Chaos 0.5 keeps breaker movement
// unpredictable, maximising simultaneous cell destruction events across 10000 frames.
// BoltCountReasonable (max 20) catches runaway bolt accumulation if Supernova's spawn cleanup
// fails. NoEntityLeaks detects orphaned shockwave request or bolt entities. BoltSpeedAccurate
// catches bolt physics corruption from simultaneous spawn events. NoNaN guards against
// position corruption from overlapping spawn origins. Max bolt count raised to 20 to
// accommodate Prism + Supernova spawns without false-positive BoltCountReasonable fires.
(
    breaker: "Prism",
    layout: "Dense",
    input: Chaos((action_prob: 0.5)),
    max_frames: 10000,
    disallowed_failures: [NoEntityLeaks, BoltCountReasonable, BoltSpeedAccurate, NoNaN],
    allowed_failures: None,
    debug_setup: None,
    invariant_params: (max_bolt_count: 20),
    allow_early_end: false,
    seed: 2718,
    chip_selections: ["Supernova"],
)
